<title>USA: Brooks Fiber wins full Oklahoma authority.</title>
<headline>Brooks Fiber wins full Oklahoma authority.</headline>
<dateline>ST. LOUIS 1996-08-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Brook Fiber Properties Inc said Wednesday that two of its subsidiaries were granted authority to provide a full range of competitive local-exchange telecommunications services in the state of Oklahoma.</p>
<p>The Oklahoma Corporation Commission granted the authority to Brooks Fiber Communications of Oklahoma City Inc and Brooks Fiber Communications of Tulsa Inc, the company said.</p>
<p>The approval allows Brooks Fiber to expand its local offerings to include full dial-tone services.</p>
